{
  "builds": [
    {
      "src": "package.json",
      "use": "@vercel/static-build",
      "config": {
        "distDir": "dist"
      }
    }
  ],
  "rewrites": [
    { "source": "/(.*)", "destination": "/index.html" }
  ],
  "headers": [
    {
      "source": "/(.*)",
      "headers": [
        {
          "key": "Access-Control-Allow-Origin",
          "value": "*"
        },
        {
          "key": "Access-Control-Allow-Methods",
          "value": "GET, OPTIONS"
        },
        {
          "key": "Access-Control-Allow-Headers",
          "value": "Content-Type"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "github": {
    "silent": true
  },
  "buildCommand": "npm run build",
  "outputDirectory": "dist",
  "devCommand": "npm run dev",
  "installCommand": "npm install"
}
{
  "headers": [
    {
      "source": "/(.*)",
      "headers": [
        {
          "key": "X-Robots-Tag",
          "value": "all"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

## 3. **Check Bot Protection Settings**
- In Vercel Firewall settings, look for "Bot Protection"
- Disable or adjust sensitivity if it's blocking legitimate AI bots
- Whitelist specific user agents if needed

## 4. **Update robots.txt**
Create or update your `public/robots.txt` file:
```
User-agent: *
Allow: /